-    <DictionaryEntry Key="content" Value="&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a class=&amp;quot;download&amp;quot; href=&amp;quot;/file.axd?file=/Architecture/AppArchGuide2.0.pdf&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;img src=&amp;quot;/image.axd?picture=/Architecture/AppArchGuideCover.png&amp;quot; alt=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;AppArchGuide2.0.pdf (3.09 mb)&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The objective of this site is to blog&amp;amp;nbsp;my adventures collaborating with &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;ChatGPT&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; (architect), &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Codex&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; (coder), and &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Copilot&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; (pair-programming) to create a &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Blog AI&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;application with features comparable to &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;BlogEngine.Net&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;(this blog application)&amp;amp;nbsp; The code being blogged about will reside in the following GitHub projects: &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://github.com/BillKrat/vs-mcp-bridge/tree/feature/approval-apply-ui-slice&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot;&amp;gt;VS MCP Bridge&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; and&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://github.com/BillKrat/BlogAI&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Blog AI&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span style=&amp;quot;color: #ff0000;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;NEW FEATURE&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;: One of the&amp;amp;nbsp;features&amp;amp;nbsp;that we have already created is the ability for Codex to generate blogs from the underlying code - it can read the codebase, generate blogs, and create/modify/post blogs (I have to review and publish them).&amp;amp;nbsp; &amp;amp;nbsp;This allows our &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;VS MCP Bridge&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Blog AI&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; projects to always have its blogs in sync with the codebase - no feature or version creep.&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;&amp;lt;span style=&amp;quot;color: #ff0000;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;BUT&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;,&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; before we can focus totally on Blog AI, we have to first create a &amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://github.com/BillKrat/vs-mcp-bridge/tree/feature/approval-apply-ui-slice&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot;&amp;gt;VS 2026 MCP Bridge&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; so that we can code within Visual Studio using Codex.&amp;amp;nbsp; This is our active project.&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br /&amp;gt; &amp;lt;img src=&amp;quot;/image.axd?picture=/Architecture/LayeredArch.png&amp;quot; alt=&amp;quot;&amp;quot; /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&#xD;&#xA;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;Image above will be Blog AI architecture&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;" />
